From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: iTrustMidware TLCP <tlcp@inspur.com>
Date: Thu, 3 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] tlcp: add trusted boot measurement for grub2-2.12 (squashed)

Implement iTrustMidware TLCP trusted boot measurement on grub2-2.12 native
hook-based architecture, with full TPM 2.0 policy state verification and
tlcptool coordination.

Summary of changes
==================

1. Build integration (grub-core/Makefile.core.def, grub-core/Makefile.am)
   - Register kern/tlcp.c, kern/efi/tlcp.c, kern/tlcp_aes.c, kern/tlcp_sha256.c
     in the GRUB kernel build (EFI/x86_64).
   - Register all tpm2_util/* marshal files and tpm2*.c in the EFI kernel.

2. Public API (include/grub/tlcp.h)
   - grub_tpm_policy_state()       — query TPM NV + persistent handles.
   - grub_file_policy_state()      — fallback: read /boot/policy.bin.
   - grub_tpm_integrity_validation(halt) — unseal hardware/software keys,
     compare with state files; prompt passphrase on failure when halt=1.
   - grub_file_integrity_validation(halt) — infinite passphrase loop; used
     when TPM absent or supervisory-policy halt is requested.
   - grub_measure_configured_files() — extend /boot/host_st_configure.xml
     into PCR 12 via EFI TCG2 protocol.
   All five declared with EXPORT_FUNC() for GRUB moddep visibility.

3. Boot integration (grub-core/commands/boot.c)
   - grub_cmd_boot() calls grub_measure_configured_files() unconditionally.
   - Under EFI/IEEE1275: queries TPM policy, runs TPM-backed integrity check
     or file-based fallback per policy type (audit / supervisory).
   - On other platforms (i386-pc): falls through directly to file-based
     policy (grub_tpm_present() is not defined there).

4. EFI TPM2 layer (grub-core/kern/efi/tlcp.c, tpm2tis.c, tpm2nvstorage.c)
   - check_tpm_policy_state(): queries TPM_CAP_HANDLES for NV 0x01800100,
     persistent handles 0x81010100 (software) and 0x81010101 (hardware),
     reads NV content to determine audit vs. supervisory policy.
   - check_file_policy_state(): reads /boot/policy.bin as file fallback;
     clears grub_errno if file absent (no stale error state).
   - get_hardware_enc_content() / get_software_enc_content(): read
     /boot/hardware_state.bin and /boot/software_state.bin.
   - get_hardware_dec_key(): StartAuthSession → PolicyPCR(0,1,2,3,6,7) →
     Unseal(0x81010101) → FlushContext; always flushes session (including
     success path); zeroes out_data from stack after use.
   - get_software_dec_key(): same sequence for PCRs(8,9,12), handle 0x81010100.
   - grub_tlcp_efi_measure(): extends buffer into PCR via
     EFI_TCG2_PROTOCOL.hash_log_extend_event(); avoids grub_tpm_measure()
     which is in the 'tpm' module (not kernel).
   - EFI protocol calls use direct method pointers (efi_call_X removed in 2.12).
   - unmarshal_uint32() uses grub_get_unaligned32() for strict-alignment safety.

5. Core TLCP logic (grub-core/kern/tlcp.c)
   - grub_tpm_policy_state(): prefers TPM NV; falls back to file.
   - grub_tpm_integrity_validation(): reads state files, unseals keys via
     EFI layer, validates AES-128-CBC encrypted magic strings
     ("INSPUR__HARDWARE" / "INSPUR__SOFTWARE") via SHA256 HMAC comparison.
     Prompts passphrase fallback exactly once when halt=1 (no double-prompt).
   - grub_file_integrity_validation(): loops until correct passphrase entered.
   - grub_measure_configured_files(): uses grub_size_t (not int) to avoid
     truncation on large files; calls grub_tlcp_efi_measure() under EFI guard.

6. Crypto helpers
   - kern/tlcp_aes.c: AES-128-CBC implementation (no external dependency).
   - kern/tlcp_sha256.c: SHA256 implementation.
   - include/grub/tlcp_aes.h, include/grub/tlcp_sha256.h: headers.

7. TPM2 stack (include/grub/tpm20.h, kern/efi/tpm2*.c, include/grub/efi/tpm2*.h)
   - Complete TPM2 command stack: startup, session, NV, object, capability,
     integrity, enhanced-authorization.
   - tpm2_util/ unmarshal helpers for all TPM2 data types.

Policy binding summary:
  Handle 0x81010101 (hardware key) sealed to PCRs 0,1,2,3,6,7
  Handle 0x81010100 (software key) sealed to PCRs 8,9,12
  NV index  0x01800100 holds policy state (1=audit, 2=supervisory)

Runtime file paths (deployed by tlcptool, consumed by GRUB):
  /boot/policy.bin              — policy type (file fallback)
  /boot/hardware_state.bin      — AES-encrypted hardware passphrase
  /boot/software_state.bin      — AES-encrypted software passphrase
  /boot/host_st_configure.xml   — measured into PCR 12 on every boot

Tested: rpmbuild -bb grub2.spec (x86_64, i386-pc) — clean build.

---
diff --git a/grub-core/Makefile.am b/grub-core/Makefile.am
index 7953ba9..651382c 100644
--- a/grub-core/Makefile.am
+++ b/grub-core/Makefile.am
@@ -66,6 +66,7 @@ CLEANFILES += grub_script.yy.c grub_script.yy.h
 
 include $(srcdir)/Makefile.core.am
 
+KERNEL_HEADER_FILES += $(top_srcdir)/include/grub/tlcp.h
 KERNEL_HEADER_FILES += $(top_srcdir)/include/grub/backtrace.h
 KERNEL_HEADER_FILES += $(top_srcdir)/include/grub/cache.h
 KERNEL_HEADER_FILES += $(top_srcdir)/include/grub/command.h
diff --git a/grub-core/Makefile.core.def b/grub-core/Makefile.core.def
index 694ae6d..746ab98 100644
--- a/grub-core/Makefile.core.def
+++ b/grub-core/Makefile.core.def
@@ -223,6 +223,38 @@ kernel = {
   efi = kern/acpi.c;
   efi = kern/efi/acpi.c;
   efi = kern/efi/sb.c;
+  common = kern/tlcp.c;
+  common = kern/tlcp_sha256.c;
+  common = kern/tlcp_aes.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2tis.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2getcapability.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2startup.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2session.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2nvstorage.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2object.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2context.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2enhancedauthorization.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2integrity.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_BASES.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPML_CCA.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPML_PCR_SELECTION.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMS_PCR_SELECTION.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMU_SYM_KEY_BITS.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMA_ALGORITHM.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPML_CC.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPML_TAGGED_TPM_PROPERTY.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMS_TAGGED_PCR_SELECT.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMU_SYM_MODE.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMA_CC.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPML_ECC_CURVE.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMS_ALG_PROPERTY.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPMS_TAGGED_PROPERTY.c;
+  efi = kern/efi/tpm2_util/tpm2unmarshal_TPML_TAGGED_PCR_PROPERTY.c;
